\vspace{2pt}
\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=0.6cm, label={\textbullet}]
    \item Designed end-to-end machine learning system for \textbf{multi-dimensional demand forecasting} using NYC 311 service data, applying time-series analysis and predictive modeling to forecast service volumes across 10 categories, directly applicable to banking operations such as call center staffing and credit demand prediction.
    \vspace{-2pt}
    \item Implemented \textbf{Temporal Fusion Transformer} and Prophet models for hourly demand forecasting, achieving 23\% lower MAPE than baseline through feature engineering (time-of-day, seasonality, service mix), model validation, and hyperparameter optimization, with attention mechanisms revealing key demand drivers for business interpretation.
    \vspace{-2pt}
    \item Developed \textbf{Bayesian optimization framework} for workforce allocation, reducing simulated wait times by 34\% and labor costs by 18\%; delivered interactive Streamlit dashboard for real-time scenario analysis and Pareto-optimal trade-off visualization between service quality and operational efficiency.
\end{itemize}
